<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Bromus</i> <i>tectorum</i>, <i>Taeniatherum</i> <i>caput</i>-<i>medusae</i> and/or <i>Ventenata</i> <i>dubia</i> is dominant or co-dominant with other non-natives in the herbaceous layer. Emergent shrubs may be present at low cover. </div>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Herbs < 1 m; cover is open to continuous. </div>
</div>

        
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Membership Rules</h4>
	<ul class="text">
		
		<li><i>Bromus tectorum</i> > 30% relative cover in the herbaceous layer (White 1994a).</li>
		
		<li><i>Bromus tectorum</i> > 50% relative cover in the herbaceous layer (Klein and Evens 2005).</li>
		
		<li><i>Taeniatherum caput-medusae</i> > 30% relative cover in the herbaceous layer (Hickson et al. 2008).</li>
		
		<li>Stand with >75% relative cover of non-native herbs and grasses such as <i>Bromus tectorum</i>, <i>Taeniatherum caput-medusae</i>, <i>Ventenata dubia</i>, and <i>Poa bulbosa</i> (Boul et al. 2021b).</li>
		
	</ul>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Abandoned fields, eroded areas, overgrazed rangeland, road verges, waste places, foothills, lower montane slopes.  </div>
</div>

        
