<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Fire Characteristics</h4>
	<div class="text"><i>Bromus tectorum </i>greatly increases the potential and reoccurrence of fires. In many areas invaded by <i>B. tectorum, </i>the fire cycle is 3 to 5 years. Not only are fires more frequent, but they are uniform, with fewer patches of unburned plants (Whisenant 1990). This shortened fire cycle considerably reduces the viability of perennials and promotes <i>B. tectorum </i>dominance (Carpenter and Murray 2005, Young 2000, Zouhar 2003a).</div>
	<table class="zebraStripe">
		
